"```sql\nSELECT \n    (SUM(CASE WHEN m.label = '+' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) * 100.0 / COUNT(b.bond_id)) AS proportion_carcinogenic\nFROM \n    bond b\nJOIN \n    connected c ON b.bond_id = c.bond_id\nJOIN \n    atom a1 ON c.atom_id = a1.atom_id\nJOIN \n    atom a2 ON c.atom_id2 = a2.atom_id\nJOIN \n    molecule m ON b.molecule_id = m.molecule_id\nWHERE \n    b.bond_type = '-'\n```\nThis SQL query calculates the proportion of single bonds (where `bond_type = '-'`) that are associated with carcinogenic molecules (where `label = '+'`). The result is expressed as a percentage."